### `++gnom`

Display ship name

Fetches a ship's display name from %ames.

## Accepts

`our` is a [`@p`]().

`now` is a [`@da`]().

`him` is a [`@p`]().

## Source

```
++  gnom                                                ::  ship display name
  |=  [[our=@p now=@da] him=@p]  ^-  @t
  =+  yow=(scot %p him)
  =+  pax=[(scot %p our) %name (scot %da now) yow ~]
  =+  woy=((hard ,@t) .^(%a pax))
  ?:  =(%$ woy)  yow
  (rap 3 yow ' ' woy ~)
::
```

## Examples

```
~zod/main=> (gnom [->-< -<-] ~zod)
'~zod |Tianming|'
~zod/main=> (gnom [->-< -<-] ~doznec)
'~doznec ~doznec'
~zod/main=> (gnom [->-< -<-] ~tug)
'~tug |Go-Daigo|'
```

